{
  "analysis": "Only 1 difference remains out of 1,440,000 values - at pixel (432,300) red channel: ref=76, mine=77. This is a floating-point precision issue in the sphere shading. I need to match the exact order of operations from the disassembly. Key insights from the disassembly: the sphere_intersect computes oc·oc as (oc.y² + oc.x²) + oc.z² (not oc.x² + oc.y² + oc.z²), and the diffuse dot product may use a different addition order. I also need to view the missing line 41 of sphere_intersect and check the exact diffuse computation order.",
  "plan": "View the missing sphere_intersect line 41 (between addresses 402258-40225b) and the exact diffuse dot product order in main. Then update the C code to match the exact floating-point operation order and test again.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "perl -e 'open(F,\"/app/mystery\");binmode F;seek F,0x2258,0;read(F,$b,8);printf \"%s\\n\",join(\" \",map{sprintf \"%02x\",$_}unpack(\"C8\",$b));'\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "objdump -d /app/mystery | sed -n '/402253:/,/40225b:/p'\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat -n /tmp/main.dis | sed -n '93,112p'\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    }
  ]
}
